display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex> be a mixed Hodge structure.
    The <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[W_n(H_\mathbb {Z})]]></fr:tex>, endowed with the filtrations induced by <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[W]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex>, then form mixed Hodge substructures <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[W_n(H)]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex>.
    The quotient <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[W_n(H)/W_{n-1}(H)]]></fr:tex> can be identified with <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Gr}_n^W(H_\mathbb {Z})]]></fr:tex> endowed with its mixed Hodge structure (<fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-ii-2.3.2"
href="hodge-theory-ii-2.3.2.xml"
number="2.3.2" /> and <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-ii-2.3.3"
href="hodge-theory-ii-2.3.3.xml"
taxon="Example"
number="2.3.3" />).
    We denote this Hodge structure by <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Gr}_n^W(H)]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
